<section class="page-header"><div class="section-inner"><div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> / Facility</div><div class="section-label">Facility &amp; Process</div><h1>Inside Our Facility</h1><p>From scrap intake to finished product, every zone is designed for efficiency, safety, and environmental compliance.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="section-inner"><div class="section-label">Facility Zones</div><h2 class="section-title">Where the Transformation Happens</h2><p class="section-desc">Our Kamunting facility is organized into dedicated processing zones.</p><div class="grid-3"><div class="zone-card"><div class="zone-img">&#128230;</div><div class="zone-body"><h3>Scrap Storage Zone</h3><p>Incoming scrap stored with proper organization, weighing, and safety protocols.</p></div></div><div class="zone-card"><div class="zone-img">&#128269;</div><div class="zone-body"><h3>Scrap Sorting Zone</h3><p>Sorting by polymer type, grade, and contaminant level. Non-rubber isolated.</p></div></div><div class="zone-card"><div class="zone-img">&#9881;</div><div class="zone-body"><h3>Granulation Zone</h3><p>Rubber transformed into uniform granules using industrial equipment.</p></div></div><div class="zone-card"><div class="zone-img">&#128736;</div><div class="zone-body"><h3>Milling &amp; Sheeting</h3><p>Milling machinery produces sheets and compounds for manufacturing.</p></div></div><div class="zone-card"><div class="zone-img">&#128295;</div><div class="zone-body"><h3>Steel Baling Zone</h3><p>Steel friction and bead wire baled using hydraulic presses.</p></div></div><div class="zone-card"><div class="zone-img">&#128666;</div><div class="zone-body"><h3>Export Zone</h3><p>Products inspected, packaged, containerized with B3040 documentation.</p></div></div></div></div></section>
<section class="bg-dark"><div class="section-inner"><div class="section-label">The Process</div><h2 class="section-title">Our Waste-to-Product Process</h2><p class="section-desc">A proprietary workflow transforming waste into high-value resources.</p><div class="process-steps"><div class="process-step"><div class="step-num">01</div><h4>Intake &amp; Documentation</h4><p>Weighed, photographed, tracked, and Basel-coded.</p></div><div class="process-step"><div class="step-num">02</div><h4>Sorting &amp; Segregation</h4><p>SBR, NR, BR, steel, nylon separated by trained operators.</p></div><div class="process-step"><div class="step-num">03</div><h4>Processing &amp; Value-Add</h4><p>Granulated, milled, or compounded to buyer specs.</p></div><div class="process-step"><div class="step-num">04</div><h4>QC, Pack &amp; Export</h4><p>Quality inspection, Annex VII docs, shipment tracking.</p></div></div></div></section>
<section class="bg-light"><div class="section-inner"><div class="section-label">Equipment &amp; Capacity</div><h2 class="section-title">Processing Capabilities</h2><div class="grid-2" style="margin-top:2rem"><div><div class="card placeholder" style="margin-bottom:1.25rem"><h3>Equipment List</h3><p>Client: Provide major equipment list (mills, granulators, balers, shredders, scales).</p></div><div class="card placeholder"><h3>Annual Capacity</h3><p>Client: Confirm annual processing capacity in metric tons.</p></div></div><div><div class="card placeholder" style="margin-bottom:1.25rem"><h3>Facility Size</h3><p>Client: Facility area (sq ft/acres), buildings, covered vs open.</p></div><div class="card placeholder"><h3>Workforce</h3><p>Client: Employee count, shifts, training certifications.</p></div></div></div><div class="questions-box"><h3>&#9888; Information Needed — Facility</h3><ol><li>Photos/videos of each facility zone</li><li>Equipment list with specs</li><li>Facility total area</li><li>Annual/monthly capacity</li><li>Employee count and shifts</li><li>Environmental monitoring setup</li><li>Safety record</li><li>QC/lab testing procedures</li></ol></div></div></section>
